The paper is about developing a compressed sensing framework for quantitative MRI using a random pulse excitation sequence and a random EPI subsampling strategy. This involves solving an inverse problem to recover proton density, T1, T2, and off-resonance maps from a limited number of samples. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.MR (Magnetic Resonance Imaging), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.IT (Information Theory) as these fields are closely related to image processing and signal reconstruction. Additionally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also possible categories as the paper uses an iterative projection algorithm and simulations to support their results.
